==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: broom corn
<hw>broom" corn`</hw></mhw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A tall variety of grass (<spn>Sorghum
vulgare</spn> <varn>technicum</varn>), having a joined stem, like maize,
rising to the height of eight or ten feet, and bearing its seeds on a
panicle with long stiff branches, of which brooms are made.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

